HB 4107
1 name, assumed business name, fictitious business name or other designation that includes
2 the terms “urgent” or “urgent care”; or
3 (B) Use the term “urgent” or “urgent care” in any external sign or advertisement.
4 (b) The prohibitions described in paragraph (a) of this subsection do not apply to a spe-
5 cialty urgent care center that uses the term “urgent” or “urgent care” in conjunction with
6 the term for the specialty medical care that the specialty urgent care center provides.
7 (3) An urgent care center shall publish on a website operated by or on behalf of the ur-
8 gent care center, and post near the main public entrance of the urgent care center in a
9 manner that is conspicuous, accessible and legible, the following information:
10 (a) The legal name of the urgent care center and any name under which the urgent care
11 center does business;
12 (b) The street address of the urgent care center;
13 (c) Any health care facility or health system affiliated with the urgent care center;
14 (d) The hours and days of operation for the urgent care center;
15 (e) The types of payment and types of payers accepted by the urgent care center;
16 (f) The services offered at the urgent care center and whether X-ray or laboratory ser-
17 vices are available at the urgent care center;
18 (g) The limitations on the availability of services;
19 (h) The types of licensed health care providers that are available at the urgent care
20 center;
21 (i) Whether the urgent care center serves patients only by walk-in or by either appoint-
22 ment or walk-in;
23 (j) The diagnostic capabilities available at the urgent care center, at a facility adjacent
24 or in close proximity to the urgent care center or by referral to another facility with the
25 location of that facility or the distance of that facility from the urgent care center; and
26 (k) Any telemedicine services offered by the urgent care center.
27 (4)(a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, an urgent care center shall,
28 at a minimum, have one licensed health care provider on site during the hours that the ur-
29 gent care center is open and be capable of providing on site the following services:
30 (A) Tests for common respiratory diseases;
31 (B) 12-lead electrocardiogram (ECG);
32 (C) Splints for strains, sprains and fractures; and
33 (D) Sutures for simple lacerations.
34 (b) An urgent care center may operate temporarily without a licensed health care pro-
35 vider on site if:
36 (A) A licensed health care provider is unavailable to be on site due to illness, emergency
37 or similar circumstance;
38 (B) A licensed health care provider is available to offer services through telemedicine;
39 and
40 (C) The urgent care center notifies a patient at the first point of contact with the patient
41 that services will be provided through telemedicine.
42 (5) If an urgent care center refers a patient to an emergency department, the urgent
43 care center shall provide the emergency department with the patient’s records that include
44 the clinical reason for the referral. The urgent care center may provide the records:
45 (a) By using a health information exchange; or
