1 (b) If the urgent care center does not participate in a health information exchange, by:
2 (A) Providing the patient with a physical copy of the records, including the clinical reason
3 for the referral; or
4 (B) Other immediate means, including a telephone call, facsimile or electronic trans-
5 mission.
6 (6) An urgent care center may not:
7 (a) Hold the urgent care center out to the public as providing emergency department
8 services; or
9 (b) Use the word “emergency” or the letters “E.R.” or “E.D.” or any derivative of the
10 word “emergency” that would lead a reasonable person to believe an urgent care center is
11 a hospital emergency department.
